 Variables:** Starch uptake g/m2, Starch uptake by paper Top/Bottom Roll g/m2, Concentration starch working tank 1, Moisture after SpeedSizer\n\n**Findings:**\n- Decreased starch uptake correlates with cost increases across all grades\n- Grade 6010100 shows largest starch uptake decrease (-2.69 g/m2)\n- Reduced concentration in starch working tank 1 consistently drives cost reduction\n- Lower moisture after SpeedSizer reduces costs (grade 6010100: -1.69%)\n\n#### Pre Dryier Section\n**Key Variables:** Speed, Speed PD1, Vacuum uhle-box bottom felt, Linepressure shoe press bar, Lip settings\n\n**Findings:**\n- Speed increases strongly correlate with cost reduction (grade 6010100: +162.10 m/min)\n- Decreased vacuum uhle-box bottom felt reduces costs\n- Reduced linepressure shoe press bar increases costs\n- Optimized lip settings contribute to cost reduction (grade 6010100: -1.32)\n\n#### After Dryier Section\n**Key Variables:** DG4 Temperature Inlet Air, Cylinder steam pressures, Cylinder differential pressures\n\n**Findings:**\n- Lower DG4 inlet air temperature reduces costs (grade 6010085: -12.03°C)\n- Increased DG4 temperature increases costs (grades 6010100, 6010120: +24-26°C)\n- Cylinder pressure optimization varies by grade, requiring careful management [papermaking_science_technology.pdf:d6f6f20ccb65b658:4601:0]\n\n#### Press Section\n**Key Variables:** Dewatering top wire suction box zone 2, Dissolved gas before dilution water deculator\n\n**Findings:**\n- Increased dewatering suction (+176.09) paradoxically increases costs for grade 6010085\n- Improved dissolved gas management (+0.25) reduces costs\n\n#### Scanner Section\n**Key Variables:** Current reel moisture average, Moisture before SpeedSizer\n\n**Findings:**\n- Decreased reel moisture (grade 6010120: -0.21%) increases costs, suggesting over-drying\n- Moisture profile optimization critical for cost-quality balance\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\n### Primary Issues\n\n1. **Grade 6010100 Overprocessing Crisis**: 12.81% overprocessing driven by excessive CMT30
